A photorealistic portrait of an Asian man in his 30s standing alone on a quiet Singapore street at golden hour, his reflection visible in a rain-puddle below, wearing casual weekend clothes, the warm sunset light casting long shadows across weathered shophouse facades behind him, humid tropical atmosphere with faint steam rising from the wet pavement, shallow depth of field focusing on his contemplative expression while the colonial architecture softly blurs into bokeh, intimate and personal mood suggesting a moment of quiet self-reflection.
